The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, March 01, 2004  Calcutta Column

	Examination time has clashed with pre-election fever once again this year. Blaring loudspeakers used by most political parties for campaigning are affecting preparations of the students. Politicians should refrain from using this tool to reach out to the masses. 
	Piyal Mukherjee, Lake Town. 
	Pedestrians find stretches of Jessore Road difficult to negotiate, thanks to vehicles under repair that are parked along the road by the local garages. Residents have tried reasoning with the workers but they refuse to budge. Can the authorities take steps to clear the road? 
	Sunil Banerjee, VIP Road. 

